    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">W.P.B. Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Minister of Supply</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaverbrook</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Vice President</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-29">December 29,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Vice-President</hi>: I enclose you copies of a
                    letter and two documents sent to the President by me.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d192fn1">The enclosures were copies of Beaverbrook’s letter to
                        Roosevelt, dated December 27, 1941 (<hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_328">p. 328</ref>), Beaverbrook’s memorandum enclosed with
                        that letter (<hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_329">p.
                        329</ref>), and Beaverbrook’s memorandum for Roosevelt of December 29 (<hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_334">p. 334</ref>).</note>
                </p>
                <p>The first document was sent on the 27th of December and the second document on
                    the 29th of December.</p>
                <p>If I can answer any questions, will you please let me know?</p>
                <p>I am most grateful for all the time you gave today and the patience you
                    displayed.</p>
                <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaverbrook</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
